19/12/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Justice Minister Meri Mladenovska-Gjorgjievska said Friday (16 December) that the government plans to submit the new draft electoral legislation to parliament by month's end.
She added that the ministry incorporated recommendations made by the OSCE in crafting the measures.
In other news, a Kosovo Albanian who managed to escape from a Macedonian prison in May has been recaptured, according to Skopje A1 TV.
Ramadan Shiti and two fellow inmates who fled the Sutka Prison reportedly were apprehended in the Kosovo village of Dubrava on Friday.
(A1 TV - 18/12/05;
Utrinski Vesnik, Vecer - 17/12/05;
A1 TV - 16/12/05)
